# Do Not Touch

The following files and areas must NOT be modified without explicit user approval:

- **`yarn.lock`** — never manually edit; only update via `yarn` commands
- **`.env.production`** / **`.env.development`** — contain environment config, do not change
- **`.husky/`** — git hooks configuration
- **`.github/`** — CI/CD workflows and PR templates
- **`firebase-project/`** — Firebase deployment config
- **`packages/excalidraw/components/App.tsx`** — massive orchestration file (407KB); changes here are high-risk and require careful review
- **`vercel.json`** — deployment routing config
- **`crowdin.yml`** — i18n/translation config
- **Build scripts in `scripts/`** — `buildPackage.js`, `buildBase.js`, `buildUtils.js`, `buildWasm.js`

If a task requires changes to any of the above, stop and confirm with the user first.

## How to verify

- Run `git diff --name-only` and check that none of the protected files/directories appear.
- If any protected file was changed, confirm it was explicitly requested by the user.
- Pay special attention to `App.tsx` changes — review with extra care due to high blast radius.
